## Adding Overlays\
\
### Option A: With Keynote (free, on Mac)  \
1. New presentation \uc0\u8594  Slide size 1290 x 2796 px  \
2. Insert screenshot as background image  \
3. Add text box at the top with overlay text (white, bold, shadow)  \
4. Optional: Add background gradient at the top (dark \uc0\u8594  transparent)  \
5. Export as PNG  \
\
### Option B: With Figma / Canva (free)  \
1. Frame: 1290 x 2796  \
2. Drag in screenshot  \
3. Add text + gradient overlay  \
4. Export as PNG  \
\
### Option C: Ready-made Templates  \
- https://screenshots.pro (free)  \
- https://mockuphone.com (device frames)  \
\
